blue borage
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Echium vulgare</i> viper's bugloss [f. its blue flower resembling the borage (<i>Borago officinalis</i>) in colour (mainly SI, esp. Marlborough and n. Cant.); also blue borage; a local (esp. Marlborough) name for the blue-flowered Eng. weed viper's bugloss.




