Quote:  The main source of nectar in this wild and remote area, flanked by the high mountains of the Seaward and Inland Kaikouras, is viper's bugloss (<i>echium vulgare</i>). Mountain-honey was the first company in New Zealand to market this kind of honey as blue borage, which is the local common name for the plant.
